  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nFoundryup\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [x] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nfoundryup: installing foundry (version nightly, tag nightly-59f026fc492ea09f2c640917f960e697d6e120b5) foundryup: downloading latest forge and cast ######################################################################################################################### 100.0% foundryup: downloading manpages ######################################################################################################################### 100.0% foundryup: installed - forge 0.2.0 (59f026f 2023-05-24T00:05:48.067515000Z) foundryup: installed - cast 0.2.0 (59f026f 2023-05-24T00:05:48.067515000Z) foundryup: done\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge test -vvvvv --match-test invariant_\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nThe latest version of Foundry breaks invariant test suites that work with previous versions.\r\n\r\nWith `fail_on_revert=true`, ssertions fail despite there being no assertions in the handler actions:\r\n```\r\n[FAIL. Reason: Assertion failed.]\r\n        [Sequence]\r\n                sender=0xe3bc896cd3d9a8292ee9e7907fe3ada211349122 addr=[test/invariants/Handler2.t.sol:Handler2]0x2e234dae75c793f67a35089c9d99245e1c58470b calldata=pokeBlockchain(), args=[]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe stack trace appears to show no reverts either:\r\n\r\n```\r\n invariant_printGhosts() (runs: 1, calls: 1, reverts: 1)\r\nTraces:\r\n  [5984066] Invariants::setUp() \r\n    ├─ [4997650] → new LimitOrderRegistry@0x5615dEB798BB3E4dFa0139dFa1b3D433Cc23b72f\r\n    │   ├─ emit OwnershipTransferred(user: 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000, newOwner: Invariants: [0x7FA9385bE102ac3EAc297483Dd6233D62b3e1496])\r\n    │   └─ ← 24601 bytes of code\r\n    ├─ [22743] LimitOrderRegistry::setMinimumAssets(1, 0x2791Bca1f2de4661ED88A30C99A7a9449Aa84174) \r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [22743] LimitOrderRegistry::setMinimumAssets(1, 0x7ceB23fD6bC0adD59E62ac25578270cFf1b9f619) \r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [55463] LimitOrderRegistry::setupLimitOrder(0x45dDa9cb7c25131DF268515131f647d726f50608, 0) \r\n    │   ├─ [266] 0x45dDa9cb7c25131DF268515131f647d726f50608::token0() [staticcall]\r\n    │   │   └─ ← 0x0000000000000000000000002791bca1f2de4661ed88a30c99a7a9449aa84174\r\n    │   ├─ [308] 0x45dDa9cb7c25131DF268515131f647d726f50608::token1() [staticcall]\r\n    │   │   └─ ← 0x0000000000000000000000007ceb23fd6bc0add59e62ac25578270cff1b9f619\r\n    │   ├─ [251] 0x45dDa9cb7c25131DF268515131f647d726f50608::fee() [staticcall]\r\n    │   │   └─ ← 0x00000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000001f4\r\n    │   ├─ emit LimitOrderSetup(pool: 0x45dDa9cb7c25131DF268515131f647d726f50608)\r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [612290] → new Handler2@0x2e234DAe75C793f67A35089C9d99245E1C58470b\r\n    │   └─ ← 2834 bytes of code\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::startPrank(0x00000000000000000000000000000000000004d2) \r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n\r\n  [3567] Handler2::pokeBlockchain() \r\n    ├─ [0] VM::warp(1673207417 [1.673e9]) \r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::roll(37834660 [3.783e7]) \r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith `fail_on_revert=false` reverts exist, but it's impossible to trace because when this flag is flipped, no indication of any reverts reveals itself.\r\n\r\nI've resolved this locally by installing a previous commit of foundry: `e15e33a07c0920189fc336391f538c3dad53da73 `",
